    "content": "<p>Weight of a person can be expressed as a function of their age. The function usually varies from person to person. Suppose this function is identical for two brothers, and it monotonically increases till the age of 50 years and then it monotonically decreases. Let $a_1$ and $a_2$ (in years) denote the ages of the brothers and $a_1 < a_2$.</p>\n<p>Which one of the following statements is correct about their age on the day when they attain the same weight?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$a_1 < a_2 < 50$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$a_1 < 50 < a_2$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$50 < a_1 < a_2$\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Either $a_1=50$ or $a_2=50$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given : The weight function is given as monotonically increasing until age 50 and monotonically decreasing afterward.</p>\n<p>This means the maximum weight occurs at age 50.</p>\n<p>Since both brothers follow the same function, they will attain the same weight at two different ages: one before 50 and one after 50 .</p>\n<p>That is, for one brother,</p>\n<p>$a_1 < 50$, and for the other,</p>\n<p>$$ a_2 > 50 $$</p>\n<p>Hence the correct option is (B).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-ai-2025",
    "difficulty": null
  },
