    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given :</p>\n<p>A regular dodecagon (12-sided regular polygon) is inscribed in a circle of radius $\\gamma \\mathrm{cm}$ as shown is the figure below.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mdifbazp/eb54096e-9646-49bc-8898-b6b91c23c579/368ad950-691e-11f0-a474-55270c80d4b2/file-jaoe38c1mdifbazq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mdifbazp/eb54096e-9646-49bc-8898-b6b91c23c579/368ad950-691e-11f0-a474-55270c80d4b2/file-jaoe38c1mdifbazq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE AI 2025 General Aptitude - Logical Reasoning Question 3 English Explanation\"></p>\n\n<p></p><p>1.A regular dodecagon consists of 12 identical isosceles triangles, each originating from the centre.</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>2.A square can be formed using multiple isosceles triangles.</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>3.Triangles are grouped together to form a square of side $\\gamma \\mathrm{cm}$.</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>4.Bases on Standard geometric properties of a dodecagon, the minimum number of triangles repuried to formed a square can be determined.</p><p></p>\n\n<p>From dodecagonal symmetry</p>\n\n<p></p><p>3 squares can be formed.</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>Each Square repuires 3 triangles.</p><p></p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (C).</p>",
